author: Rosie McCall
title: Thousands of Pink Jellyfish Seen in the Philippines as Tourists Desert Beaches Amid Coronavirus Crisis
description: "There are years when blooms or populations of a jellyfish are high and there are also years when they are few or even almost absent," said Sheldon Rey Boco, who filmed the event.
content:
Giant blooms of pink jellyfish have been reported in Palawan, Philippines, as beaches are left deserted during the coronavirus pandemic.
